<TITLE> Injured Yuvraj ruled out of Champions Trophy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 CHENNAI, India, Sept 23 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - India batsman Yuvraj Singh will miss the Champions Trophy due to a fractured finger, the Indian cricket board (BCCI) said on Wednesday. The aggressive left-hander suffered the injury during a fielding session in Johannesburg on Wednesday, three days before his team's opening match against Pakistan. "Yuvraj Singh has fractured a finger in his right hand and has been ruled out for six weeks," the BCCI said in a statement. Virat Kohli was named as his replacement. India, one of the favourites to win the eight-team tournament, have also lost explosive opener Virender Sehwag and pace bowler Zaheer Khan to injury and are still sweating over the fitness of opener Gautam Gambhir who has a groin strain. India have been grouped with defending champions Australia, former winners West Indies and Twenty20 champions Pakistan in the preliminary p
